Do not frame this branch as target-producing unless a documented conversion from imidazole to histidine-relevant intermediates is added\",\n        \"Treat it as supporting network context rather than a true pathway to target\",\n        \"Include the second ammonia equivalent in stoichiometric annotation for Debus-Radziszewski chemistry\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.94,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.89,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.68,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.5,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.78,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.32,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.56,\n      \"feedback\": \"The HCN to DAMN to AICN to AICA branch is well grounded in prebiotic photochemistry and correctly reflects the literature connection between purine and histidine biosynthetic contexts. However, there is no demonstrated prebiotic extension from AICA/AICN to histidine, so this is not a true target pathway. It is better interpreted as chemical context rather than synthesis route.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Separate contextual imidazole chemistry from target-reaching pathways in scoring and labeling\",\n        \"Avoid suggesting that aminoimidazole intermediates feed directly into histidine without experimental evidence\",\n        \"If retained, explicitly mark the bridge to histidine as absent\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.86,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.67,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.48,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.77,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.28,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.55,\n      \"feedback\": \"The FoDHA-CN imidazole cascade is an excellent literature-based inclusion for modern prebiotic imidazole chemistry, but the network does not establish a credible conversion from its imidazole product to imidazole-4-acetaldehyde or histidine. As with the DAMN branch, this is scientifically relevant context but not an experimentally supported histidine pathway.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Classify this branch as speculative connector chemistry rather than a route to target\",\n        \"State that extension from Sutherland's imidazole products to histidine remains an open frontier\",\n        \"Do not count this branch toward target-achievement metrics unless connected by a validated transformation\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.32,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.76,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.69,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.83,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.87,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.75,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.76,\n      \"feedback\": \"This pathway is good at showing hydrothermal-to-surface crossover, which is a strength of the network design. However, it still depends on the weakest reaction in the network, hydrothermal formaldehyde generation, and it stops short of the final hydrolysis if the 6-step description is taken literally. Strong environmental logic, moderate chemical support.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_001\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Include the final hydrolysis step explicitly if this is meant to reach histidine\",\n        \"Replace or qualify the hydrothermal formaldehyde step with a better sup