for histidine (Ferris & Kuder, 1970; V\u00e1zquez-Salazar et al., 2018)."}, {"id": "rxn_014", "name": "FoDHA-CN cyanide cascade to an imidazole derivative", "inputs": ["mol_019", "mol_007"], "outputs": ["mol_020"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["sulfide minerals (stibnite/molybdenite)", "TiO2 (anatase/rutile)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "298K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "cyanide in formamide-rich alkaline medium", "aqueous": "true", "other": "pH 9.2; reported 63% yield of an imidazole derivative"}, "mechanism": "Cyanide addition initiates a cascade that forms three new C-N bonds and constructs an imidazole derivative from N-formyldehydroalanine nitrile.", "reasoning": "Green, Xu, & Sutherland (2023) reported this high-yielding imidazole-forming cascade. The deep report highlights it as a promising modern advance but explicitly states that extension to histidine or imidazole-4-acetaldehyde has not been demonstrated. It is therefore included as a connected comparative branch only."}, {"id": "rxn_015", "name": "Histidine peptide bond formation to His-His dipeptide on mineral interfaces", "inputs": ["mol_012"], "outputs": ["mol_021"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": [], "conditions": {"temperature": "330-360K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": null, "aqueous": "false", "other": "wet-dry cycling on mineral surfaces; mineral-assisted self-assembly and peptide bond formation"}, "mechanism": "Concentrated histidine on mineral interfaces self-assembles and dehydrates to form peptide bonds, giving small histidyl peptides.", "reasoning": "Madrigal-Trejo et al. (2021) showed that histidine self-assembles and forms peptide bonds on antigorite, pyrite, and aragonite surfaces, with enhanced thermal stability. White & Erickson (1981) further showed catalytic relevance of His-His in prebiotic peptide chemistry. This reaction is downstream of target formation and illustrates why even scarce histidine could have been selectively valuable."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Validated Shen-Miller-Oro histidine pathway", "description": "The sole experimentally demonstrated complete prebiotic route to histidine: erythrose and formamidine give imidazole-4-acetaldehyde by Schiff-base formation and Amadori rearrangement, followed by Strecker conversion and hydrolysis to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_011"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Hydrothermal-to-surface carbon feed into validated histidine route", "description": "Hydrothermal CO2 reduction supplies reduced carbon that is transferred to surface formaldehyde and then into the erythrose-dependent Shen pathway.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_003", "mol_004", "mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_009"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Surface sugar-supply route to erythrose bottleneck", "description": "Formaldehyde and glycolaldehyde in borate-stabilized surface chemistry converge on erythrose, the sugar precursor required for the only known histidine synthesis.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_009"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "HCN-to-formamidine feeder route into validated histidine synthesis", "description": "Surface HCN accumulation and amidine formation generate the key but prebiotically problematic formamidine reagent needed for the Shen route.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_009"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Bottleneck-only completion from imidazole-4-acetaldehyde", "description": "If the crucial intermediate imidazole-4-acetaldehyde is granted, Strecker chemistry and hydrolysis complete histidine formation efficiently relative to the difficulty of making the aldehyde.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_008", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_011"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Debus-Radziszewski imidazole context branch", "description": "A literature-supported alternative route to the imidazole ring from glyoxal, formaldehyde, and ammonia. It demonstrates easy imidazole formation but does not provide a validated path to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_014"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "HCN oligomerization to DAMN context branch", "description": "HCN tetramerization yields DAMN, a robust feeder into aminoimidazole photochemistry and a key comparison branch showing that HCN readily builds heterocycles even though histidine remains inaccessible.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "DAMN photochemistry to AICN branch", "description": "UV-driven conversion of DAMN to AICN shows near-quantitative imidazole-ring assembly from HCN oligomers under early Earth surface UV conditions.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_015", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "AICN to AICA purine-histidine evolutionary context branch", "description": "Hydrolysis of AICN to AICA links prebiotic aminoimidazole chemistry to purine intermediates and the modern metabolic intersection with histidine biosynthesis, but not to a demonstrated abiotic histidine route.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_011", "rxn_012", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_016", "mol_017"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Sutherland FoDHA-CN imidazole cascade context branch", "description": "A high-yield modern prebiotic imidazole-forming cascade from N-formyldehydroalanine nitrile and cyanide. It is included as the most promising alternative imidazole chemistry, though no extension to histidine has been demonstrated.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_014"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_020"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_0